 will lose the tuition waiver resulting from the assistantship federal immigration  regulations do not allow an international student on a student visa to register for more than zero       hours previously  unless the student is admitted into a different program hour registration occurs hour registration is allowed for students on a visa only if all requirements other than the thesis or master s project are completed  and registration for more than zero hours indicates that they did not originally qualify  and OIS  if there is a question on this issue Permission to use either Option A or B will be considered by the Graduate College upon receipt of a Graduate College Student Petition supported by the graduate program  thesis  or dissertation have been completed  On rare occaisions  a course with a grade of I  DFR  or NR may still be pending  but the DGS should note the exception on the petition  Additionally  a re evaluation of the student s status may occur  regardless of which option is chosen maximum two terms per petition  Students must re file a petition for Option B by the   th day of the term   th for summer  so that the student bill is correctly calculated Students should register via Student Self Service for project  usually      master s thesis       professional doctorate project     The following are some scenerios where a student may need to register for zero hours  Master s Students The Graduate College does not have a registration requirement for master see above  the student may petition to register for zero hours in the project  usually      or thesis      s students who are in a coursework only option are not eligible for zero hours s student s are only eligible for Zero Hours Option A   hours  tuition  tuition differential  if applicable to your program  and all related fees  including CampusCare  unless under the the opt out option   see www uic www uic edu hsc campuscare See http   www uic edu depts oar grad tuition grad http   www uic edu depts oar grad tuition grad html See also Examination and Defense Committees and Registration Examination and Defense Committees Registration Doctoral candidates must be registered for credit the term when they take the preliminary exam  however  Students must also register each semester  excluding summer  after passing the preliminary examination and until successfully defending the dissertation Students who hold a fellowship  assistantship  or tuition and fee waiver must register each semester for the number of hours required by their award  even if they have completed all degree requirements except the dissertation   See Course Loads  Financial Awards section Course Loads Doctoral students who have completed all degree requirements except the dissertation  and who do not wish to register for additional coursework  must choose either  www uic edu hsc campuscare http   www uic edu depts oar grad tuition grad html  or http   www uic edu depts oar grad tuition grad html www uic edu hsc campuscare  and must file a new petition if future terms of Option B are required i e  not paying the attached fees  if registered in one or more hours Examination and Defense Committees Registration Footer Menu Privacy Policy Support Graduate Education My UIC EDU Contact Us UIC Follow Us RSS Feed Twitter Facebook Shibboleth login Login 